
[1]curtail

   CURTAIL, v.t. [L., to cut; edge.] To shorten; to cut off the end or a
   part; as, to curtail words. Hence in a more general sense, to shorten
   in any manner; to abridge; to diminish; as, to curtail our privileges.
   It is followed by of before the thing shortened. His name was curtailed
   of three letters. We are curtailed of our rights.
